    <h1>Data Transmission within and outside Trivium</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <blockquote>
<p><em>Both the exchange of data with other entities via electronic communi=
cation networks as well as the physical transport of mobile data carriers a=
nd documents must be secured in such a way that the confidentiality and int=
egrity of personal data is not compromised. </em></p>
<p><em>In the following, we explain how data is handled within and outside =
of Trivium. </em></p>
</blockquote>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Simply because you and your colleagues work for the same company does no=
t mean that everyone has access to the same data. The opposite is true. Don=
't be afraid to ask!</p></li>
<li>
<p>Access to data must be limited to what is absolutely necessary. If you a=
re unsure about the permissions for accessing data in your area, please spe=
ak with your supervisor immediately.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Sharing data with external parties requires a high level of diligence an=
d rules for sharing.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Unauthorised disclosure of personal data may result in an obligation to =
report a personal data breach.</p></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"DataTransmissionwithinandoutsideTrivium-Internaldatatransmission"=
>Internal data transmission</h1>
<h2 id=3D"DataTransmissionwithinandoutsideTrivium-Typicalexample">Typical e=
xample</h2>
<p>An application for the development department is forwarded to an employe=
e of the marketing department, who is generally not authorised to access ap=
plicants' data. As a rule, the HR department, the management and, if applic=
able, the head of department in the respective department are responsible f=
or data processing within the scope of application processes. The principle=
s of <strong>confidentiality </strong>and <strong>purpose limitation</stron=
g> must be observed without restriction - which means that employees outsid=
e these areas of responsibility are <strong>not allowed to access</strong> =
the relevant data.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DataTransmissionwithinandoutsideTrivium-Carefulhandlingofdata">Ca=
reful handling of data</h2>
<p>To ensure adequate data protection at Trivium, it is advisable not to pa=
ss on personal data to unauthorised persons or to persons who are not respo=
nsible for the processing. It should therefore be regulated which persons o=
r departments have access to which data in order to mitigate a personal dat=
a breach.</p>
<p>It can be a good intention to provide colleagues with information - for =
example, when they ask for it. However, in any case, make sure that there i=
s no doubt about the <strong>authorisation of the requesting employee</stro=
ng>.</p>
<p>The principles of <strong>confidentiality </strong>and <strong>purpose l=
imitation </strong>must be fully observed - which means that employees outs=
ide of these responsibilities must not have access to the relevant data.</p=
>
<h1 id=3D"DataTransmissionwithinandoutsideTrivium-Datatransmissiontoexterna=
lparties">Data transmission to external parties</h1>
<p>The transfer of data to external parties (e.g. to the tax consultant or =
to a client) via electronic communication networks as well as the physical =
transport of mobile data carriers and documents must be secured in such a w=
ay that the confidentiality and integrity of the personal data is not compr=
omised.</p>
<p>To ensure these requirements, mobile data carriers should be <strong>enc=
rypted </strong>according to state-of-the-art technology. For e-mail and cl=
oud platforms, transport encryption and content encryption of personal data=
 are recommended (see <a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2878472198/Secure+E=
mail+Communication" data-linked-resource-id=3D"2878472198" data-linked-reso=
urce-version=3D"8" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Secure Email Communic=
ation</a>).</p>
<h1 id=3D"DataTransmissionwithinandoutsideTrivium-Usetherighttools">Use the=
 right tools</h1>
<p>For any business related internal and external digital communication the=
 accounts and tools / services provided by Trivium must be used on company =
as well as your own devices. Examples are</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Email, Calendar, Contacts: Trivium email address and Outlook</p></li>
<li>
<p>Meetings and chats: Microsoft Teams</p></li>
<li>
<p>File exchange: Microsoft Onedrive or <a class=3D"external-link" data-car=
d-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://share.trivium-esolutions.de/" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://share.trivium-esolutions.de/</a></p></li>
<li>
<p>Password exchange: Keeper (<a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearan=
ce=3D"inline" href=3D"https://docs.keeper.io/en/user-guides/self-destructin=
g-records" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.keeper.io/en/user-guides/self-dest=
ructing-records</a>)</p></li>
</ul>
<p>If there are project-specific differences, these must be taken into acco=
unt. This includes, for example, the provision of e-mail addresses or other=
 communication platforms by the client.</p>
<h1 id=3D"DataTransmissionwithinandoutsideTrivium-Consequencesofunauthorize=
ddisclosure">Consequences of unauthorized disclosure</h1>
<p>Any form of carelessness and negligence when disclosing personal data ca=
n result in legal sanctions, such as fines.</p>
<p>Anyone who discloses personal data unlawfully interferes intensively wit=
h the data subject's rights. Therefore, you must check whether your disclos=
ure actions are lawful according to Art. 6 of the General Data Protection R=
egulation (GDPR) and whether the recipient is also authorised to do so befo=
re such disclosure.</p>
<p>Even if an unauthorised person gains access to personal data, a personal=
 data breach pursuant to Art. 33 of the GDPR has occurred. Depending on the=
 severity of the consequences for the data subject and the likelihood of oc=
currence, this may even lead to an obligation to report to the supervisory =
authority concerned.</p>
